SIMPLE: twenty
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twenty
<hw>Twen"ty</hw> <pr>(tw⟦ecr⟧n"t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>twenty</ets>, AS. <ets>tw⟦emac⟧ntig</ets>, <ets>twentig</ets>; akin
to OFries. <ets>twintich</ets>, OS. <ets>tw⟦emac⟧ntig</ets>, D. & LG.
<ets>twintig</ets>, OHG. <ets>zweinzug</ets>, G. <ets>zwanzig</ets>,
Goth. <ets>twai tigjis</ets>; that is, two tens. See <er>Twain</er>,
<er>Two</er>, and <er>Ten</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One more than
nineteen; twice ten; <as>as, <ex>twenty</ex> men</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An indefinite number more or less that twenty.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Maximilian, upon <qex>twenty</qex> respects, could not have been
the man.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twenty</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Twenty
<hw>Twen"ty</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Twenties</plw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The number next following
nineteen; the sum of twelve and eight, or twice ten; twenty units or
objects; a score.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A symbol representing twenty units, as 20, or
xx.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twentyfold</ent>⟦br⟧
